T1  - Investor Networks in the Stock Market
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hht065
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 27
IS  - 5
SP  - 1323
EP  - 1366
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study the trading behavior of investors in an entire stock market. Using an account level dataset of all trades on the Istanbul Stock Exchange in 2005, we identify investors with similar trading behavior as linked in an empirical investor network (EIN). Consistent with the theory of information networks, we find that central investors earn higher returns and trade earlier than peripheral investors with respect to information events. Overall, our results support the view that information diffusion among the investor population influences trading behavior and returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hht065
ER  - 



